00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:20.940 align:middle line:84%
How is it even possible to
rewire our system as adults?

00:02:20.940 --> 00:02:22.740 align:middle line:84%
It's possible
because of something

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:24.970 align:middle line:90%
called neuroplasticity.

00:02:24.970 --> 00:02:27.420 align:middle line:84%
This exciting
discovery was actually

00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:31.410 align:middle line:84%
made by neuroscientists
starting as early as the 1800s.

00:02:31.410 --> 00:02:33.990 align:middle line:84%
Prior to that time, it was
believed that the brain

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:37.920 align:middle line:90%
was hardwired by the age of 25.

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.990 align:middle line:84%
But since the '70s,
scientists have

00:02:39.990 --> 00:02:43.830 align:middle line:84%
continued to discover just
how adaptable our brain

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:46.620 align:middle line:90%
and nervous system really are.

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:48.540 align:middle line:84%
They found that
our neural wiring

00:02:48.540 --> 00:02:52.090 align:middle line:84%
is malleable throughout
our lifetime.

00:02:52.090 --> 00:02:54.930 align:middle line:10%
This is what
neuroplasticity means.

00:02:54.930 --> 00:02:57.900 align:middle line:84%
Even though the deeper
core wiring of the brain

00:02:57.900 --> 00:03:01.980 align:middle line:84%
may be set by the age
of 25, the good news

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:05.910 align:middle line:84%
is that we can still
redirect and rewire it

00:03:05.910 --> 00:03:10.820 align:middle line:84%
through our choices, our
attitudes, and our actions.

00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:12.520 align:middle line:90%
How does this work?

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:15.070 align:middle line:84%
When we read most
books or articles

00:03:15.070 --> 00:03:18.220 align:middle line:84%
that discuss rewiring
our brain, they typically

00:03:18.220 --> 00:03:21.650 align:middle line:90%
emphasize a few key things.

00:03:21.650 --> 00:03:26.440 align:middle line:84%
Number one, focused
attention, such as when

00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:29.290 align:middle line:84%
we take on a
challenging new task,

00:03:29.290 --> 00:03:33.220 align:middle line:84%
like learning a new language
or a musical instrument.

00:03:33.220 --> 00:03:36.850 align:middle line:84%
The second thing is
repetition and practice,

00:03:36.850 --> 00:03:39.820 align:middle line:84%
making it into a
daily habit that we

00:03:39.820 --> 00:03:42.730 align:middle line:90%
integrate as part of our life.

00:03:42.730 --> 00:03:44.650 align:middle line:84%
Research has shown
that it's only

00:03:44.650 --> 00:03:49.660 align:middle line:84%
after about 90 to 144
straight days of practice

00:03:49.660 --> 00:03:53.980 align:middle line:84%
that a new behavior becomes
more firmly wired in.

00:03:53.980 --> 00:03:58.960 align:middle line:84%
Until then, it takes motivation,
willpower, discipline,

00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:01.840 align:middle line:84%
and self-control
to follow through

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:05.930 align:middle line:84%
on achieving that new
skill or behavior.

00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:09.190 align:middle line:84%
Another thing we need is
the right environment,

00:04:09.190 --> 00:04:12.730 align:middle line:84%
one that is conducive
to learning and change.

00:04:12.730 --> 00:04:14.410 align:middle line:84%
The right environment
includes things

00:04:14.410 --> 00:04:18.700 align:middle line:84%
like having supportive and
harmonious relationships,

00:04:18.700 --> 00:04:22.870 align:middle line:84%
good physical health,
and the ability to relax.

00:04:22.870 --> 00:04:27.220 align:middle line:84%
If we're too stressed, our brain
kicks into its fight or flight

00:04:27.220 --> 00:04:34.330 align:middle line:84%
survival mode, and it defaults
to old neural patterns.

00:04:34.330 --> 00:04:38.190 align:middle line:84%
Let's explore now how we can
take this deeper so that we

00:04:38.190 --> 00:04:42.210 align:middle line:90%
can truly attain self mastery.

00:04:42.210 --> 00:04:45.810 align:middle line:84%
Our intention with this is
to expand our consciousness,

00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:48.510 align:middle line:84%
access those
transcendent states,

00:04:48.510 --> 00:04:51.930 align:middle line:84%
and harness our
greater capacity.

00:04:51.930 --> 00:04:54.810 align:middle line:84%
We start with the
part of our brain

00:04:54.810 --> 00:04:58.110 align:middle line:84%
that we have the most
conscious control of--

00:04:58.110 --> 00:05:01.030 align:middle line:90%
namely, the prefrontal cortex.

00:05:01.030 --> 00:05:04.140 align:middle line:84%
This part of the brain
that scientists call

00:05:04.140 --> 00:05:07.290 align:middle line:90%
"our executive control center."

00:05:07.290 --> 00:05:10.980 align:middle line:84%
This area is highly connected
to the other brain regions.

00:05:10.980 --> 00:05:15.510 align:middle line:84%
Thus, it can govern them
through top down processing.

00:05:15.510 --> 00:05:20.460 align:middle line:84%
It oversees our decision making,
control over our impulses,

00:05:20.460 --> 00:05:24.930 align:middle line:84%
and it gives us the ability
to act with intention.

00:05:24.930 --> 00:05:28.620 align:middle line:84%
The prefrontals sit right behind
the forehead and a little bit

00:05:28.620 --> 00:05:32.580 align:middle line:84%
up from there, coinciding with
the front part of the crown

00:05:32.580 --> 00:05:34.530 align:middle line:90%
and forehead head area.

00:05:34.530 --> 00:05:38.280 align:middle line:84%
How we can use this
knowledge of its location

00:05:38.280 --> 00:05:43.230 align:middle line:84%
is by tapping on this area to
stimulate it in a rhythmic way.

00:05:43.230 --> 00:05:48.870 align:middle line:10%
For example, tapping the third
eye or just above the eyebrows

00:05:48.870 --> 00:05:53.790 align:middle line:10%
or even up in the hairline
can stimulate our prefrontals.

00:05:53.790 --> 00:05:58.860 align:middle line:84%
So when and how does our
prefrontal cortex develop?

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:01.950 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns out that this
is actually the last part

00:06:01.950 --> 00:06:03.630 align:middle line:90%
of the brain to develop.

00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:07.170 align:middle line:84%
That's because it's the most
recent addition to the brain's

00:06:07.170 --> 00:06:09.390 align:middle line:90%
evolution on Earth.

00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:12.490 align:middle line:84%
Now it happens in two
stages of human growth.

00:06:12.490 --> 00:06:16.500 align:middle line:84%
The first stage occurs
from birth to age 15.

00:06:16.500 --> 00:06:19.590 align:middle line:84%
This primary stage of
prefrontal development

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:23.890 align:middle line:84%
happens in parallel with the
rest of the brain structures.

00:06:23.890 --> 00:06:27.450 align:middle line:10%
Now because of this, it
becomes highly connected to all

00:06:27.450 --> 00:06:29.940 align:middle line:10%
the other brain regions.

00:06:29.940 --> 00:06:33.480 align:middle line:84%
The extent of this
connectivity and functionality

00:06:33.480 --> 00:06:37.320 align:middle line:84%
depends on our experiences,
our environment,

00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:41.700 align:middle line:84%
and our social interactions
during our developmental years.

00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:44.070 align:middle line:10%
The early wiring
in our prefrontals

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:50.860 align:middle line:10%
is crucial to us, becoming
balanced, well-adjusted adults.

00:06:50.860 --> 00:06:53.020 align:middle line:84%
Now, the second
phase of development

00:06:53.020 --> 00:06:56.870 align:middle line:90%
continues from age 15 to 25.

00:06:56.870 --> 00:06:59.050 align:middle line:84%
And at this stage,
the early connections

00:06:59.050 --> 00:07:01.810 align:middle line:84%
have become more
deeply rooted, but now

00:07:01.810 --> 00:07:05.920 align:middle line:84%
the prefrontal themselves
continue to grow and develop

00:07:05.920 --> 00:07:09.520 align:middle line:90%
more abstract capabilities.

00:07:09.520 --> 00:07:12.430 align:middle line:84%
It's only in our teen
and early adult years

00:07:12.430 --> 00:07:15.670 align:middle line:84%
that we become able
to reason with more

00:07:15.670 --> 00:07:18.430 align:middle line:90%
complexity and forethought.

00:07:18.430 --> 00:07:23.660 align:middle line:84%
This is why proper education
is so important at this time.

00:07:23.660 --> 00:07:26.760 align:middle line:84%
Now what else are our
prefrontals in charge of?

00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:30.320 align:middle line:84%
In short, they orchestrate
the rest of the brain,

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:33.520 align:middle line:84%
connecting into all the
other regions and layers.

00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:35.720 align:middle line:84%
Connecting into the
cerebral cortex,

00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:38.120 align:middle line:84%
then down into
the limbic system,

00:07:38.120 --> 00:07:40.860 align:middle line:84%
and down even into
the old brain.

00:07:40.860 --> 00:07:43.490 align:middle line:84%
And while the driving
force of our will

00:07:43.490 --> 00:07:47.570 align:middle line:84%
comes through the mind with
our goals, our intentions,

00:07:47.570 --> 00:07:51.530 align:middle line:84%
and choices, it is
our prefrontal cortex

00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:56.230 align:middle line:84%
that orchestrates the
brain-body system.

00:07:56.230 --> 00:07:59.380 align:middle line:84%
So what's the key to
specifically rewiring

00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:01.240 align:middle line:90%
the prefrontals?

00:08:01.240 --> 00:08:06.430 align:middle line:84%
It has to do with what is known
as hemispheric transfer, which

00:08:06.430 --> 00:08:09.890 align:middle line:84%
relates to the fact that we have
two hemispheres in the brain--

00:08:09.890 --> 00:08:12.280 align:middle line:90%
the right and the left lobes.

00:08:12.280 --> 00:08:14.770 align:middle line:84%
While they look
similar, evolution

00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:19.960 align:middle line:84%
has developed them into two
distinct processing styles.

00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:22.180 align:middle line:84%
These two hemispheres
have sometimes

00:08:22.180 --> 00:08:25.090 align:middle line:84%
been described as
a team of rivals,

00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:28.930 align:middle line:84%
processing the world through
dual streams of attention.

00:08:28.930 --> 00:08:33.100 align:middle line:84%
They perceive in
very different ways.

00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:37.330 align:middle line:84%
In our left hemisphere tends
to be more linear, logical,

00:08:37.330 --> 00:08:40.690 align:middle line:90%
structured, and detail-oriented.

00:08:40.690 --> 00:08:45.430 align:middle line:84%
Our right hemispheres more big
picture, gestalt, creative,

00:08:45.430 --> 00:08:47.020 align:middle line:90%
and artistic.

00:08:47.020 --> 00:08:48.760 align:middle line:84%
It's the side of
us that connects

00:08:48.760 --> 00:08:53.970 align:middle line:84%
more to nature and
relationships and having fun.

00:08:53.970 --> 00:08:56.860 align:middle line:84%
And while we may think
of these two hemispheres

00:08:56.860 --> 00:09:00.520 align:middle line:84%
as polar opposites,
the truth is that they

00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:05.440 align:middle line:84%
are meant to work together
for a whole brain experience.

00:09:05.440 --> 00:09:09.100 align:middle line:84%
Both the right and
left modes of operation

00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:13.690 align:middle line:84%
are necessary for becoming
a balanced and well-adjusted

00:09:13.690 --> 00:09:16.010 align:middle line:90%
person.

00:09:16.010 --> 00:09:18.680 align:middle line:84%
But unfortunately,
most people tend

00:09:18.680 --> 00:09:22.010 align:middle line:84%
to have imbalances between
these two hemispheres,

00:09:22.010 --> 00:09:24.880 align:middle line:84%
with one dominating
over the other.

00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:28.520 align:middle line:84%
And in Western society, we
tend to put much more emphasis

00:09:28.520 --> 00:09:31.490 align:middle line:84%
on the left brain
way of doing things.

00:09:31.490 --> 00:09:35.720 align:middle line:84%
As a result, our modern world
has become very left brain

00:09:35.720 --> 00:09:37.310 align:middle line:90%
dominant.

00:09:37.310 --> 00:09:43.370 align:middle line:84%
Values like reason,
logic, science, IQ,

00:09:43.370 --> 00:09:47.660 align:middle line:84%
being organized and disciplined
and thinking rationally

00:09:47.660 --> 00:09:51.980 align:middle line:84%
tend to be more emphasized
in society today.

00:09:51.980 --> 00:09:55.070 align:middle line:84%
These have been placed
above the more right brain

00:09:55.070 --> 00:10:01.490 align:middle line:84%
qualities of EQ, nurturing,
artistic expression, empathy,

00:10:01.490 --> 00:10:03.350 align:middle line:90%
intuition.

00:10:03.350 --> 00:10:05.720 align:middle line:84%
And because of this,
we live in a world

00:10:05.720 --> 00:10:10.550 align:middle line:84%
that currently places less
value or emphasis on whole brain

00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:12.110 align:middle line:90%
development.

00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:15.320 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, this is
starting to change again,

00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:17.000 align:middle line:84%
but it's taking
time for the shift

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:20.270 align:middle line:84%
to really reach our
societal institutions,

00:10:20.270 --> 00:10:22.460 align:middle line:90%
like our education system.

00:10:22.460 --> 00:10:26.930 align:middle line:84%
Our education system has been on
a trend of cutting out the art

00:10:26.930 --> 00:10:30.960 align:middle line:84%
and music programs, while
emphasizing math, science,

00:10:30.960 --> 00:10:32.990 align:middle line:90%
and standardized testing.

00:10:32.990 --> 00:10:37.160 align:middle line:84%
This leads to an unbalanced
programming and wiring

00:10:37.160 --> 00:10:41.600 align:middle line:84%
of our brains from the moment
that we enter grade school.

00:10:41.600 --> 00:10:45.950 align:middle line:84%
The ideal is not to be right
or left brain dominant,

00:10:45.950 --> 00:10:48.830 align:middle line:90%
but to be whole brain.

00:10:48.830 --> 00:10:52.100 align:middle line:84%
Between the two
hemispheres is a wide band

00:10:52.100 --> 00:10:56.210 align:middle line:84%
of nerve fibers known
as the corpus callosum.

00:10:56.210 --> 00:11:01.080 align:middle line:84%
What we want is to have
good connectivity here.

00:11:01.080 --> 00:11:04.340 align:middle line:84%
And there are methods
we can use to develop

00:11:04.340 --> 00:11:08.840 align:middle line:84%
a more balanced and
connected whole brain.

00:11:08.840 --> 00:11:11.960 align:middle line:10%
In Kabbalah, this is
equivalent to balancing

00:11:11.960 --> 00:11:17.250 align:middle line:10%
the two pillars of mercy and
severity on the tree of life.

00:11:17.250 --> 00:11:20.870 align:middle line:84%
What this means is that we
have to work on ourselves

00:11:20.870 --> 00:11:23.120 align:middle line:90%
to achieve that balance.

00:11:23.120 --> 00:11:25.670 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to
happen if we just

00:11:25.670 --> 00:11:28.310 align:middle line:84%
keep doing things how
we've always done them.

00:11:28.310 --> 00:11:31.130 align:middle line:84%
In our present state,
we experience life

00:11:31.130 --> 00:11:33.680 align:middle line:84%
through a set of
filters, and we tend

00:11:33.680 --> 00:11:37.640 align:middle line:84%
to default to relying
on our strengths,

00:11:37.640 --> 00:11:40.400 align:middle line:84%
while avoiding our
weaknesses But this only

00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:43.100 align:middle line:90%
reinforces the imbalance.

00:11:43.100 --> 00:11:45.440 align:middle line:84%
If we want to bring
balance, we have

00:11:45.440 --> 00:11:49.970 align:middle line:84%
to choose to stimulate
the brain in new ways.

00:11:49.970 --> 00:11:52.550 align:middle line:84%
We can create new
neural connections

00:11:52.550 --> 00:11:56.630 align:middle line:84%
to strengthen the areas
we're not as strong in.

00:11:56.630 --> 00:11:59.840 align:middle line:10%
Working on our weaknesses
to bring them up

00:11:59.840 --> 00:12:03.330 align:middle line:10%
to the same level
as our strengths.

00:12:03.330 --> 00:12:05.690 align:middle line:84%
This balances and
builds the bridges

00:12:05.690 --> 00:12:09.320 align:middle line:90%
between the two hemispheres.

00:12:09.320 --> 00:12:13.910 align:middle line:84%
Our prefrontals are what give
us humans the ability to engage

00:12:13.910 --> 00:12:15.130 align:middle line:90%
with the world.

00:12:15.130 --> 00:12:19.540 align:middle line:84%
And because of it, we have
become a powerful species.

00:12:19.540 --> 00:12:23.420 align:middle line:84%
It is what gives us the
ability to act upon our ideals,

00:12:23.420 --> 00:12:26.270 align:middle line:84%
rather than just our
animal instincts.

00:12:26.270 --> 00:12:29.000 align:middle line:84%
One author and psychologist,
Iain McGilchrist,

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:32.390 align:middle line:84%
explores this relationship
between the two hemispheres

00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:36.470 align:middle line:84%
extensively in his book, "The
Master and His Emissary."

00:12:36.470 --> 00:12:40.700 align:middle line:84%
McGilchrist sums up the
prefrontal and their defining

00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:43.190 align:middle line:90%
role in the human experience.

00:12:43.190 --> 00:12:48.200 align:middle line:84%
He said, it made us the most
powerful and destructive

00:12:48.200 --> 00:12:49.520 align:middle line:90%
animals.

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:52.730 align:middle line:10%
It has also turned us
into the social animal

00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:56.390 align:middle line:10%
and into an animal with
a spiritual dimension.

00:12:56.390 --> 00:13:00.140 align:middle line:84%
Now, the reason that the
prefrontals are the gateway

00:13:00.140 --> 00:13:03.770 align:middle line:84%
is because by intentionally
stimulating this area,

00:13:03.770 --> 00:13:08.090 align:middle line:84%
it automatically sends signals
to the rest of the brain

00:13:08.090 --> 00:13:09.960 align:middle line:90%
and nervous system.

00:13:09.960 --> 00:13:13.280 align:middle line:84%
This aids us in developing
stronger neural connections

00:13:13.280 --> 00:13:14.870 align:middle line:90%
throughout the brain.

00:13:14.870 --> 00:13:18.620 align:middle line:84%
And in addition, by using
methods such as meditation

00:13:18.620 --> 00:13:22.010 align:middle line:84%
to expand consciousness,
we can also

00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:24.640 align:middle line:90%
access transcendent states.

00:13:24.640 --> 00:13:26.990 align:middle line:90%
So how does this work?

00:13:26.990 --> 00:13:31.620 align:middle line:84%
Well, the general motto is, what
fires together wires together.

00:13:31.620 --> 00:13:35.330 align:middle line:84%
This is how our neural
pathways are built.

00:13:35.330 --> 00:13:38.480 align:middle line:84%
When a stimulus comes
in, it triggers a feeling

00:13:38.480 --> 00:13:42.170 align:middle line:84%
in the body, which then
triggers a response that

00:13:42.170 --> 00:13:47.390 align:middle line:84%
is based either on our ego's
desires or our body's needs.

00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:51.170 align:middle line:84%
This ultimately then leads
to a thought pattern.

00:13:51.170 --> 00:13:55.030 align:middle line:84%
All of this is firing
off neurons in the brain.

00:13:55.030 --> 00:13:59.060 align:middle line:84%
And the more certain triggers
and patterns fire together,

00:13:59.060 --> 00:14:03.350 align:middle line:84%
the more the neural pathway
is built or reinforced.

00:14:03.350 --> 00:14:07.220 align:middle line:84%
When repeated enough,
this creates strong wiring

00:14:07.220 --> 00:14:09.200 align:middle line:90%
along that pathway.

00:14:09.200 --> 00:14:11.570 align:middle line:84%
And through
repetition, information

00:14:11.570 --> 00:14:15.065 align:middle line:84%
is exchanged across
the synaptic gaps.

00:14:15.065 --> 00:14:18.320 align:middle line:84%
And the more the synapses
exchange information,

00:14:18.320 --> 00:14:22.830 align:middle line:84%
the more they then rearrange
to move closer together.

00:14:22.830 --> 00:14:26.210 align:middle line:84%
This allows for greater ease
of information exchange,

00:14:26.210 --> 00:14:28.910 align:middle line:84%
and this is true for
both our positive wiring

00:14:28.910 --> 00:14:30.890 align:middle line:90%
and our negative wiring.

00:14:30.890 --> 00:14:34.610 align:middle line:84%
Meaning our good habits
and our bad habits.

00:14:34.610 --> 00:14:38.180 align:middle line:84%
The more we access a
certain pattern or emotion,

00:14:38.180 --> 00:14:42.380 align:middle line:84%
the stronger that connection
becomes, making it easier

00:14:42.380 --> 00:14:45.560 align:middle line:90%
to continue accessing.

00:14:45.560 --> 00:14:49.490 align:middle line:84%
So what can we do when we
have a negative pattern?

00:14:49.490 --> 00:14:54.350 align:middle line:84%
If our brain has wiring towards
negativity or unhealthy default

00:14:54.350 --> 00:14:58.880 align:middle line:84%
patterns, we can rewire
it to more positive ones.

00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:03.560 align:middle line:84%
First, we must identify
what we want to replace

00:15:03.560 --> 00:15:06.530 align:middle line:90%
the negative tendency with.

00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:10.640 align:middle line:84%
Have a strategy in place for the
new pattern or thought process

00:15:10.640 --> 00:15:13.160 align:middle line:90%
that we want to reinforce.

00:15:13.160 --> 00:15:17.150 align:middle line:10%
For example, if we tend to
be pessimistic or judgmental

00:15:17.150 --> 00:15:19.670 align:middle line:10%
about ourselves or
the world, we can

00:15:19.670 --> 00:15:23.000 align:middle line:10%
choose to replace it with
an attitude of gratitude

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.810 align:middle line:10%
and acceptance.

00:15:24.810 --> 00:15:30.110 align:middle line:84%
Then, start listing the things
that we are grateful for.

00:15:30.110 --> 00:15:34.190 align:middle line:84%
The second thing is that we
must catch ourselves in the act.

00:15:34.190 --> 00:15:36.590 align:middle line:84%
When we find ourselves
in an old pattern,

00:15:36.590 --> 00:15:39.470 align:middle line:84%
we have to interrupt
it and redirect

00:15:39.470 --> 00:15:42.740 align:middle line:84%
to the more positive wiring
that we wish to implement.

00:15:42.740 --> 00:15:45.620 align:middle line:84%
When a pattern is
repeatedly interrupted,

00:15:45.620 --> 00:15:49.010 align:middle line:84%
the synapses stop
firing together.

00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:53.480 align:middle line:84%
And in time, they
disconnect the old pathway.

00:15:53.480 --> 00:15:58.430 align:middle line:84%
So first, be prepared for what
you are going to do, and then

00:15:58.430 --> 00:16:01.340 align:middle line:84%
do it any time
you catch yourself

00:16:01.340 --> 00:16:04.830 align:middle line:84%
in that old negative
pattern or thought.

00:16:04.830 --> 00:16:08.190 align:middle line:84%
This is how we
replace the old habits

00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:11.040 align:middle line:90%
with new, more supportive ones.

00:16:11.040 --> 00:16:13.380 align:middle line:84%
We want to be
intentional about it.

00:16:13.380 --> 00:16:15.870 align:middle line:90%
It will take some effort.

00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:19.020 align:middle line:84%
Rewiring and instilling
new behaviors and skills

00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:22.710 align:middle line:84%
takes practice,
focus, and energy.

00:16:22.710 --> 00:16:26.610 align:middle line:84%
We must repeat and repeat
over and over again,

00:16:26.610 --> 00:16:28.350 align:middle line:84%
interrupting that
old pattern and then

00:16:28.350 --> 00:16:31.080 align:middle line:90%
replacing it with a new one.

00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:36.010 align:middle line:84%
Through that dedication,
consistency, and willpower,

00:16:36.010 --> 00:16:38.860 align:middle line:90%
we make the shift.

00:16:38.860 --> 00:16:43.000 align:middle line:84%
At some point, once it's
been reinforced sufficiently,

00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:47.440 align:middle line:84%
it then becomes an
integrated pattern or habit.

00:16:47.440 --> 00:16:50.410 align:middle line:84%
We are, after all,
creatures of habit.

00:16:50.410 --> 00:16:53.110 align:middle line:90%
It's part of our nature.

00:16:53.110 --> 00:16:57.940 align:middle line:84%
Let's just be conscious and
intentional about those habits.

00:16:57.940 --> 00:17:00.970 align:middle line:84%
Rather than operating through
our programming or default

00:17:00.970 --> 00:17:05.410 align:middle line:84%
coping strategies to determine
how we react to life,

00:17:05.410 --> 00:17:08.560 align:middle line:84%
we can become proactive
to build habits

00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:12.589 align:middle line:84%
that support us in achieving
our full potential.

00:17:12.589 --> 00:17:17.200 align:middle line:84%
This strategy is where we
start the process of mastering

00:17:17.200 --> 00:17:19.849 align:middle line:90%
our own body's wiring.

00:17:19.849 --> 00:17:22.930 align:middle line:84%
As we rewire, we
enhance our ability

00:17:22.930 --> 00:17:27.670 align:middle line:84%
to access our full potential
and build a stronger foundation

00:17:27.670 --> 00:17:29.670 align:middle line:90%
to live from.

00:17:29.670 --> 00:17:34.280 align:middle line:84%
It takes effort to live
consciously and intentionally.

00:17:34.280 --> 00:17:37.170 align:middle line:84%
But at some point,
it gels, becoming

00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:40.260 align:middle line:90%
an automatic way of life.

00:17:40.260 --> 00:17:42.750 align:middle line:84%
Much of this happens
through having

00:17:42.750 --> 00:17:47.100 align:middle line:84%
a daily spiritual practice,
whether that practice

00:17:47.100 --> 00:17:53.100 align:middle line:84%
is meditation, yoga,
qigong, prayer, or rituals.

00:17:53.100 --> 00:17:54.580 align:middle line:84%
In the mystery
school traditions,

00:17:54.580 --> 00:17:57.540 align:middle line:84%
we make a pattern of
living that includes

00:17:57.540 --> 00:18:02.110 align:middle line:84%
daily rituals to establish a
flow of energy through our day.

00:18:02.110 --> 00:18:06.480 align:middle line:84%
This includes meditation
to quiet the neural firings

00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:10.680 align:middle line:84%
and bring in a higher level
of spiritual awareness.

00:18:10.680 --> 00:18:13.110 align:middle line:84%
And when the mind is
quiet, we can then

00:18:13.110 --> 00:18:17.580 align:middle line:84%
begin to fire new neural
circuits that relate

00:18:17.580 --> 00:18:20.610 align:middle line:90%
to higher spiritual impulses.

