Remember, our brain is a
receiver, processing input

00:18:25.140 --> 00:18:28.110 align:middle line:90%
from vibrational energies.

00:18:28.110 --> 00:18:30.330 align:middle line:84%
By understanding
how this operates,

00:18:30.330 --> 00:18:34.170 align:middle line:84%
we can intentionally use
the right vibrational inputs

00:18:34.170 --> 00:18:38.130 align:middle line:84%
to stimulate our brain
in a harmonious way.

00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:41.670 align:middle line:84%
One way to do this is by working
with brainwave entrainment

00:18:41.670 --> 00:18:42.930 align:middle line:90%
methods.

00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.770 align:middle line:84%
To understand how
these tools work,

00:18:44.770 --> 00:18:49.230 align:middle line:84%
let's first explore what
brainwaves really are.

00:18:49.230 --> 00:18:52.110 align:middle line:84%
The neural networks
of the brain oscillate

00:18:52.110 --> 00:18:54.420 align:middle line:90%
as they fire together.

00:18:54.420 --> 00:18:58.980 align:middle line:84%
Brainwaves are synchronized
neural oscillations.

00:18:58.980 --> 00:19:01.680 align:middle line:84%
They're not just about
a single neuron firing

00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:05.310 align:middle line:84%
across the synapse, but
groupings of neurons

00:19:05.310 --> 00:19:08.260 align:middle line:90%
firing together in a network.

00:19:08.260 --> 00:19:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And this creates
a chain reaction

00:19:09.930 --> 00:19:12.420 align:middle line:84%
of firings between all
of the neural pathways

00:19:12.420 --> 00:19:13.890 align:middle line:90%
that are connected.

00:19:13.890 --> 00:19:15.840 align:middle line:84%
The result is a
wave pattern that

00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:19.810 align:middle line:84%
flows through the connected
sections of the brain.

00:19:19.810 --> 00:19:23.490 align:middle line:84%
And these neural oscillations
can range between frequencies

00:19:23.490 --> 00:19:26.760 align:middle line:90%
of 0, up to 100 Hertz.

00:19:26.760 --> 00:19:29.100 align:middle line:10%
The deepest brainwave
state is called

00:19:29.100 --> 00:19:35.100 align:middle line:10%
delta, which vibrates
between 0.1 to 3 Hertz.

00:19:35.100 --> 00:19:36.840 align:middle line:84%
And this state
usually corresponds

00:19:36.840 --> 00:19:41.400 align:middle line:84%
to really deep, slow
wave sleep, one in which

00:19:41.400 --> 00:19:43.560 align:middle line:90%
we're not dreaming.

00:19:43.560 --> 00:19:46.910 align:middle line:84%
When in a delta, we're
typically unconscious.

00:19:46.910 --> 00:19:50.760 align:middle line:84%
A delta state allows for
the pruning of our neurons

00:19:50.760 --> 00:19:55.300 align:middle line:84%
and synaptic connections that
are not being used anymore.

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:59.850 align:middle line:84%
So a good night's sleep
is essential for the brain

00:19:59.850 --> 00:20:03.690 align:middle line:84%
to have its opportunity
to clean up.

00:20:03.690 --> 00:20:07.980 align:middle line:10%
Next is the theta brainwave
state, just above delta,

00:20:07.980 --> 00:20:13.170 align:middle line:10%
which isolates between 3 to
8 Hertz or beats per second.

00:20:13.170 --> 00:20:16.740 align:middle line:10%
Theta is a deep
meditative state,

00:20:16.740 --> 00:20:18.990 align:middle line:10%
and it rests at
the border between

00:20:18.990 --> 00:20:21.970 align:middle line:10%
conscious and unconscious.

00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:26.070 align:middle line:84%
This is the brainwave level that
we want to access and sustain

00:20:26.070 --> 00:20:28.440 align:middle line:90%
while in meditation.

00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:30.760 align:middle line:84%
Typically, without a
strong meditation practice

00:20:30.760 --> 00:20:34.980 align:middle line:84%
though, we only experience theta
during that brief transition

00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:37.630 align:middle line:90%
between waking and sleeping.

00:20:37.630 --> 00:20:40.990 align:middle line:84%
And while in theta, we
may experience colors,

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:44.910 align:middle line:84%
shapes, images flashing
through our mind's eye.

00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:48.720 align:middle line:84%
It's a dreamy state, where the
ego mind is out of the way,

00:20:48.720 --> 00:20:52.360 align:middle line:84%
and yet, we still maintain
some level of awareness.

00:20:52.360 --> 00:20:55.880 align:middle line:90%


00:20:55.880 --> 00:21:00.530 align:middle line:84%
What about using activities
like yoga, tai chi, or qigong.

00:21:00.530 --> 00:21:03.470 align:middle line:10%
Typically, these
more active methods

00:21:03.470 --> 00:21:08.090 align:middle line:10%
are good tools for getting into
an alpha state, but not a theta

00:21:08.090 --> 00:21:09.440 align:middle line:10%
state.

00:21:09.440 --> 00:21:13.790 align:middle line:10%
Alpha brainwaves, which
oscillate between 8 to 13

00:21:13.790 --> 00:21:15.530 align:middle line:10%
Hertz, they're good too.

00:21:15.530 --> 00:21:19.940 align:middle line:10%
They help to relieve stress
and bring relaxation.

00:21:19.940 --> 00:21:23.210 align:middle line:10%
Things like light
meditation, guided imageries,

00:21:23.210 --> 00:21:26.090 align:middle line:10%
a relaxing shower,
and daydreaming

00:21:26.090 --> 00:21:29.030 align:middle line:10%
all tend to put us
into an alpha state.

00:21:29.030 --> 00:21:32.960 align:middle line:84%
Here, we can be tuned into
guidance and spiritual

00:21:32.960 --> 00:21:36.380 align:middle line:84%
awareness, while still
having our mind engaged

00:21:36.380 --> 00:21:38.720 align:middle line:84%
and being aware of
the outer world.

00:21:38.720 --> 00:21:43.540 align:middle line:84%
But that also means that the
ego can still engage as well.

00:21:43.540 --> 00:21:46.000 align:middle line:84%
Only in the deeper
theta and delta

00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:49.090 align:middle line:84%
states is the ego
out of the way.

00:21:49.090 --> 00:21:50.980 align:middle line:84%
The deeper we go,
the more we feel

00:21:50.980 --> 00:21:55.300 align:middle line:84%
connected to the universal
mind, and our sense of self

00:21:55.300 --> 00:22:01.240 align:middle line:84%
dissolves, and we become
one with all that is.

00:22:01.240 --> 00:22:04.360 align:middle line:84%
How about the higher
brainwave states?

00:22:04.360 --> 00:22:08.620 align:middle line:10%
Between 13 to 32 Hertz
is what we call beta.

00:22:08.620 --> 00:22:11.530 align:middle line:10%
This is actually our
typical waking state,

00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:14.500 align:middle line:10%
where we're engaged
with the outside world.

00:22:14.500 --> 00:22:18.070 align:middle line:84%
Beta is when we're more
alert and actively focusing

00:22:18.070 --> 00:22:21.010 align:middle line:84%
on the things that
are external to us.

00:22:21.010 --> 00:22:23.170 align:middle line:84%
The good thing about
beta is that when

00:22:23.170 --> 00:22:27.550 align:middle line:84%
we want to learn new information
from an outside source,

00:22:27.550 --> 00:22:32.090 align:middle line:84%
it helps us to be in a
harmonized beta state.

00:22:32.090 --> 00:22:34.600 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, in
our world today, we

00:22:34.600 --> 00:22:38.050 align:middle line:84%
tend to operate in an
unbalanced beta state,

00:22:38.050 --> 00:22:40.690 align:middle line:84%
with too many chaotic
inputs stimulating us

00:22:40.690 --> 00:22:42.520 align:middle line:90%
from the outside.

00:22:42.520 --> 00:22:45.130 align:middle line:84%
When we learn to
harmonize the hemispheres

00:22:45.130 --> 00:22:48.340 align:middle line:84%
and access a whole
brain beta state,

00:22:48.340 --> 00:22:53.320 align:middle line:84%
that is when new information can
come in and really take root.

